ConsoleCommunicationsBox
public class CommunicationsBox extends HoloBase
UI element hosting a text box for user input, and a log box for incoming output.

    • onExit

      public void onExit(Callback<CommunicationsBox.ExitType> callback)
      Called when the communications box is withdrawn from the screen. Callback takes an CommunicationsBox.ExitType parameter.

      This method is called when the communications box is exited via ESCAPE or explicitly defined exit button, or when the communications box is interrupted by a game event or interruption.

      See Also:
      • CommunicationsBox.ExitType.INTENDED
      • CommunicationsBox.ExitType.INTERRUPTED

    • onSendInput

      public void onSendInput(Callback<String> callback)
      Called when the user sends input from the input field. Callback takes a String parameter.

      This method is called when the user presses ENTER after inputting text into the input field.
